      • findPeaks

        public void findPeaks(int minAmp,
             int minShoulder,
             int minRelaxedShoulder,
             int minDist)
        Calculates the set of peak intensities and positions of the channel
        Parameters:
        minAmp - Minimum allowed amplitude for peaks
        minShoulder - Minimum allowed amplitude for shoulder peaks
        minRelaxedShoulder - Relaxed Minimum allowed amplitude for shoulder peaks.
        N.B. this is only applied after a certain scan index
        minDist - Minimum allowed distance between peaks

        Searches for a single peak over a specified range
        Parameters:
        searchLimit1 - start array index
        searchLimit2 - end array index
        Returns:

      • isAdjacentPeak

        private boolean isAdjacentPeak(java.util.ArrayList peakPosList,
                     int position,
                     int direction)
        Asks if there is a close peak on either the lhs or rhs contained in the input list, wrt an input peak position. n.b. spacing < Constants.AVERAGE_BASE_SPACING-2
        Parameters:
        peakPosList - ArrayList of peak positions
        position - scan position of peak to query
        direction - direction indicator for peak (PEAK_TO_LEFT or PEAK_TO_RIGHT)
        Returns:
        boolean result
